caption: Great sushi and even better ramen!

Google maps listing says Dine-in. We called to check if they had Patio seating and they confirmed that they did. Then we drove out to them and walked in to get seated and two members of staff looked at each other and hesitatingly said "uh, no we don't have patio seating actually".  I'm not sure what made them change their mind, but this is outrageous service and this restaurant needs to sort theirselves out.
Awesome ramen. Ordered tonight for the first time tonight and will be ordering again soon.
Very sweet people & ambiance. The sushi is amazing! We had the 911 sushi tempura, dynamite, & California roll. Will definitely come back again!
incredible local spot.  very fresh fish and unique flavors.  haven't had a bad thing here.

Loved this little Ramen spot. It was a quaint little place in Lincoln Park. They are Covid Safe. The servers were friendly. The Panko Crusted Chicken Ramen was delightful. The pork belly "steam" buns were amazing and their octopus balls reminded me of conch fritters,  which I LOVE!
I love it soo much 🍽
Terrible food, unpleasant staff and rude owner.
Food was ok, but my main concern was the cleanliness of the restaurant

We just moved to the neighborhood and googled best Ramen in Chicago. Kameya came up so we figured we’d give it a try. We ordered the Kameya (pork) Ramen. This is by far the BEST ramen I’ve ever had living in this city. The broth is pure magic - super flavorful and rich. I’d recommend adding the garlic spice as it’s not that spicy and gives the broth a nice kick. The pork was melt in your mouth, not too fatty but super tender. You need to try this place now! Ordered online through their website and super easy pickup.
Such a great spot! Great service, great food, and very fast. I will definitely be back!

I got the Kameya Ramen and it has a unique broth, nothing like I've had before and it was delicious. The staff was polite, but my only complaint was that it took a long time to get a table and to get our food. I was done with my ramen by the time my date's sushi got there.

I celebrated my nomination today in this fine place. happy to tell that it was a delightful evening and the venue was surely one of the reasons for that fruitful meeting. The crew  participated in a pleasant way, the food was very good and my buddies were so  pleased. We shall no dout return for more events. thanks very much.

My boyfriend and I came here and were absolutely blown away by the pork belly ramen. You can tell the people who own this place pay attention to the quality of the ingredients they use to ensure a fantastic flavor. The super friendly server brought us the best green tea ice cream we’ve ever had! They also expanded their menu to include sushi as well, also super quality! We will back back to try more the chicken ramen and take advantage of the BYOB option.
Amazing sushi ! I had the A combo and it was delicious. Generous amount of fish, great cuts.

The sushi was soooooo tasty. Full of interesting flavors. Each roll was unique and delicious. We were honestly floored and really wish we were local to enjoy it again and again. Great service and cute place, but amazing sushi.
Tiny spot but the food is excellent.
Excellent sushi and a wonderful ambiance. Loved it.
japanese food and the feeling here is quality. The food was amazing. Mood here is similar to Fresno's scene.
One of my favorite sushi spots in the city for an inexpensive,  casual meal ans great food.
Quality sushi
Nice atmosphere and friendly staff. The fish they use for their Sushi strikes out, definitely better than at most of the Sushi places.
I love this place , the food is so delicious and affordable price
Best food and service will recommend to family and friends!!!!

This is a small, cozy  and very affordable restaurant. The food it's tasty and fresh, our server was very knowledgeable of the menu and very attentive. Everything came out quickly and this was the best ramen bowl I've ever had in Chicago! I'll be going there again!
3 of us enjoyed super fresh sushi rolls and the best bowl of ramen we thought in last decade 😊

Small sushi and ramen spot. We split a few sushi rolls. The rolls we're tasty and appropriately priced for the quality.  The restaurant is a little cramped. The wait staff were disorganized. Was distracting to have the servers trying to squeeze past each other.  Table near the door gets blasted by a fan. We asked to move and another group asked to move while we were there.
Amazing ramen, however the restaurant is very small so the wait might be long!
Great ramen bowls!

Such a delicious restaurant with authentic Japanese ramen. The place is affordable and very relaxing for a good dinner with friends and family. The staff are great and quick with their job and we felt very welcomed.

Almost don't want to write a review, so people don't know about this hidden gem. LOVE the mango martini roll. Great spot for a cozy date night and for take-out. Great staff working and high quality sushi!
Great service, and delicious authentic Japanese food
Best sushi I have had in Chicago. Very quiet, romantic atmosphere. Great for a nice out with a special someone, or for a delicious meal with friends.
One of my favorites in Chicago. A cute hole in the wall. Get the pork buns! The tuna tower is great as well and their sushi is fresh and tasty.
Fresh fish and good quality sushi.

(Translated by Google) Worst sushi in the world, very expensive, and horrible. Don't go man! Worst sushi ever .. To expensive and bad. Just don't.  (Original) Pior sushi do mundo, muito caro, e horrível. Não vai cara! Worst sushi ever.. To expensive and bad. Just don't.
We had an amazing time here! The food was delicious and the service was truly stellar. One of the best experiences I've had at a restaurant.
Went here back in early Nov, 2017 but it was closed for remodeling.  They're back open now and it's a fantastic place to grab sushi, or ramen.
Very good sushi!!
Best sushi in Chicago. Not over-the-top, just really high quality, fresh ingredients, expertly prepared and great service!
The best Sushi, consistently,  I've had in Chicago.
Food was great and we had a very friendly waitress everything was fresh
the tuna tartar is the bomb! must have!!
Yum! Good wine, yummy cheese ball appetizer and delicious rolls. Tiny spot with no more than ten tables. Wouldn't recommend for a group but a cute spot to meet a friend!

Decent, basic sushi but overpriced. I'd give this place 4 stars if it were a third cheaper. A rainbow roll shouldn't cost $15 and be of average quality. And a dinner that cost me almost $60 for 4 menu items and was not entirely filling left me a bit disappointed. I would have given this place 2.5 stars but they were nice enough, so rounded up instead of down. Pork buns were good, not great. Wanted to support a local restaurant but don't think I need to go back. Was worth a try. I know the restaurant biz is tough and margins are tight, but still too expensive for what it is.
Love this place!  Maybe 20 seats total, but large menu and interesting sushi. The tuna tower is a must get. We usually get the sushi sashimi plate as well. This is our go-to sushi place.
Great little neighborhood sushi joint.  Sat outside on the sidewalk.  The Kameyo house roll was delicious.
Everything is Just great, we come here for dinner. We order two ramen( beef and seafood) and tofu bibimbop...since we have child, so we order everything less salty, and they turn out excellent!!
Great small sushi joint with friendly service
Fantastic food and service!

Hot Pot Bibimbap was delicious - honestly it had enough flavor already to the point where I felt I didn't really need to add the beef. And the crispy rice from the hot pot took it to the next level. The sauce you add yourself is also so tasty. My friend really liked his sushi as well.

Very intimate place with good service.  High quality food.  Small menu but every item is on point.  If you don't like raw fish, they have other good buns and cooked items. If you don't like the fattening version of ramen, then this place has the best clear broth ramen in town.  (But remember, it's not the creamy thick brother version... it's clean and clear and I assume less calories than the other kind of ramen).
The people that work here are the sweetest. The ramen was great, very flavourful. Would definitely recommend for Japanese and some Korean food! Will definitely be back!
The sushi is a cut above most places in the area, and the bibimbap is also quite good
Cozy and fair priced 7 table joint. Highly recommend.
Cozy atmosphere and friendly staff! Don't forget to try their homemade almond ice cream.
Amazing, the staff was the friendliest people I've ever been around, the food was wonderful, I just loved it
A bit hidden, but very good sushi in an intimate, cozy environment.
Wonderful atmosphere, friendly staff, and delicious sushi. Not the cheapest place in the world, but good sushi rarely is. Go at an off time for a lovely, cozy, and calm spot in the busy city.
Really tasty sushi. Small, though, so you're not always able to get a table. Get takeout!
Great place to eat!!! I love how the restaurant layout. It feels like I am in Japan. It is a small place but very cozy. Food is Awesome!!! Recommended who visits Chicago!!
I  came   in  this   kameya   Korean  and   Japanese   restaurant    too   weeks   ago,,   ate   sushi,    and   sashimi,,  seafood   ramen   noodles   soup,   so   delicious,,,,,   amazing,,

I love korean food. Me and my girlfriend  try Bibimbob And bulgogi AP so so nice. My next table people said kameya  ramen Is best one in chicago We will try ramen soon Highly recommend  this reastaurant! !
Good food fresh sushi, affordable price from appetizer to main dish very polite and friendly staff..

Excellent service along with very friendly and attentive staff. Ordered a wide variety of appetizers including the barbecue pork buns, bulgogi lettuce wrap, and crab cheese balls and they were all delicious. However, the cheese balls have a lot of cream cheese, not much crab taste. If you can handle spice, I would highly recommend the spicy beef ramen as your entree.
Beat sushi restaurant I ever visited in my life. :^)
We love Kameya. Best Sushi in town. Very friendly service and so far we have always had a really good experience having dinner there
It's a beautiful place that fit for couples.
Excellent Freaking Sushi
Wonderful experience, excellent sushi.
